Project Night Sky — Planetary Sky Simulation

Working name: PARALLAX ATLAS (Myth Engine optional layer)

Mission

Simulate what the sky “feels like” from different bodies in the solar system—what dominates, what hugs the Sun, what roams the whole night, and how that changes the mythic cast a civilization might invent.

Core idea

A “planet” is a viewpoint. Change the viewpoint, and the sky’s character changes.

⸻

1) Formal Spec

1.1 Inputs

A. Ephemeris model (pluggable)
	•	Tier 0 (toy): coplanar circular orbits (fast, self-contained)
	•	Tier 1: Keplerian elements (eccentricity, inclinations; still offline)
	•	Tier 2: high-precision ephemeris (JPL / SPICE, etc.)

B. Simulation config
	•	observer: body name (Earth, Mars, etc.)
	•	targets: list of bodies to render (planets + optional moons)
	•	time_span_days: e.g., 0 → 1825 days
	•	dt_days: time step (e.g., 1–10 days)
	•	visibility_threshold_deg: e.g., 10° elongation from Sun (simple “night-possible” heuristic)

1.2 Outputs

A. SkyFrame (per timestep)
A frame is “what’s in the sky from here at time t.”

{
  "t_days": 123.0,
  "observer": "Mars",
  "objects": [
    {
      "name": "Earth",
      "range_AU": 1.12,
      "elongation_deg": 35.4,
      "phase_0to1": 0.78,
      "brightness_proxy": 0.31
    }
  ]
}

B. Summary metrics (per target)
	•	visible_frac (fraction of timesteps meeting the night-heuristic)
	•	mean_bright_visible
	•	max_bright
	•	min_dist, max_dist
	•	max_elong

C. “Myth seeds” layer (optional but fun)
A deterministic mapping from metric signatures → archetypes.

Example mapping rules:
	•	Always near Sun → “Herald / Temptation / Gate-light”
	•	Whole-sky wanderer + periodic retrograde → “Warrior / King”
	•	Farthest visible naked-eye → “Boundary / Time / Gatekeeper”
	•	Dominates brightness → “Sovereign / Judge”
	•	Rarely visible → “Hidden / Whisperer”

1.3 Key derived concept: Interior vs. Exterior

For an observer at radius a_o and a target at a_t:
	•	If a_t < a_o: target is interior → stays near the Sun (Morning/Evening-star behavior)
	•	If a_t > a_o: target is exterior → can appear anywhere in the night sky (opposition behavior)

This is the deep engine behind why the ancients placed Mercury/Venus “inside” the Sun.

