2) First Test Run (Tier 0 Toy Model)

What I ran
	•	Orbits: circular, coplanar
	•	Time span: 5 Earth years
	•	Step: 5 days
	•	Visibility heuristic: elongation ≥ 10°
	•	Brightness proxy (rough but useful):
B \propto \frac{R^2 \cdot \text{phase}}{d^2}
where R is radius (Earth=1), d is observer-target distance, phase is a simple illumination proxy.

Why this is still valuable

Even if the absolute dates aren’t “astronomy-accurate,” the structural truths pop out:
	•	who hugs the Sun from where
	•	who dominates the sky brightness-wise
	•	who becomes the “Morning Star” on other worlds

