4) Bonus: Sun dominance changes by world

Sun’s apparent diameter scales ~ 1/r, brightness ~ 1/r^2 (relative to Earth).
	•	Mercury: Sun looks 2.58× larger than from Earth and ~6.68× brighter
	•	Mars: Sun looks 0.66× Earth’s, ~0.43× brightness
	•	Jupiter: Sun looks 0.19× Earth’s, ~0.037× brightness
	•	Pluto: Sun becomes a hard bright star, not a disk in your gut-feel sense

Myth implication: on the outer worlds, the Sun stops feeling like a “god-face” and starts feeling like a distant law.

